column5:
{'id': 79175928, 'author': 'hlezama', 'permlink': 'pwdynt', 'category': 'poetry', 'parent_author': 'adsactly', 'parent_permlink': 'adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers', 'title': '', 'body': 'Beautiful post, @nancibriti. A refreshing reminder of our indebtedness to high literature in our development of self and awareness.

Most people will die without having experienced poetry in their lives. They will argue that they do not need that, that probably they did better in life precisely because they did not bother to stop at "poetryland".

I think that the reason our world is the mess it is is precisely because very few people in it has stopped to contemplate the beauty of literature, which in turn would have given them some sense of introspection, so needed in this selfish world of ours.

Thank you for showcasing Palacios, a powerful voice in Venezuelan letters, unknown even for most Venezuelans. Our schools have a big work ahead to rescue all these writers from obscurity and relaunch the discovery of local literature from early age.', 'json_metadata': '{"tags":["poetry"],"users":["nancibriti"],"app":"steemit/0.1"}', 'last_update': '2019-08-17T14:52:42', 'created': '2019-08-17T14:52:42', 'active': '2019-08-18T12:29:36', 'last_payout': '2019-08-24T14:52:42', 'depth': 1, 'children': 1, 'net_rshares': 0, 'abs_rshares': 0, 'vote_rshares': 0, 'children_abs_rshares': 0, 'cashout_time': '1969-12-31T23:59:59', 'max_cashout_time': '1969-12-31T23:59:59', 'total_vote_weight': 0, 'reward_weight': 10000, 'total_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'curator_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'author_rewards': 0, 'net_votes': 0, 'root_author': 'adsactly', 'root_permlink': 'adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers', 'max_accepted_payout': '1000000.000 SBD', 'percent_steem_dollars': 10000, 'allow_replies': True, 'allow_votes': True, 'allow_curation_rewards': True, 'beneficiaries': [], 'url': '/poetry/@adsactly/adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers#@hlezama/pwdynt', 'root_title': 'ADSactly Poetry: Poetry: A Place of Many Answers', 'pending_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'total_pending_payout_value': '0.000 STEEM', 'active_votes': [], 'replies': [], 'author_reputation': '50549314926577', 'promoted': '0.000 STEEM', 'body_length': 0, 'reblogged_by': []}
column6:
{'id': 79177709, 'author': 'josemalavem', 'permlink': 'pwe1h4', 'category': 'poetry', 'parent_author': 'adsactly', 'parent_permlink': 'adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers', 'title': '', 'body': 'You dedicate a beautiful and post-sense, @nancybriti, to, undoubtedly, one of the great voices (feminine or not) of Spanish-speaking poetry (beyond Venezuelan) of the twentieth century. Antonia Palacios was (has been) one of the initiators in my sensibility and in my poetic work. I remember a poem I dedicated to her in memoriam in my second book: 

>The tremor is made
in the place you leave
Far away your name
your designs
Inadvertent inhabitant
desired in the eviction
required in absence

>Only one breath consecrates us:
your plural resonance
unattainable
question mark

The poetry loaded with vision and inner sense of Antonia Palacios, and her prose saying are the most attractive characters.  You pick them up very well in your work. Thank you for sharing.', 'json_metadata': '{"tags":["poetry"],"users":["nancybriti"],"app":"steemit/0.1"}', 'last_update': '2019-08-17T15:54:27', 'created': '2019-08-17T15:53:33', 'active': '2019-08-18T12:35:00', 'last_payout': '2019-08-24T15:53:33', 'depth': 1, 'children': 1, 'net_rshares': 0, 'abs_rshares': 0, 'vote_rshares': 0, 'children_abs_rshares': 0, 'cashout_time': '1969-12-31T23:59:59', 'max_cashout_time': '1969-12-31T23:59:59', 'total_vote_weight': 0, 'reward_weight': 10000, 'total_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'curator_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'author_rewards': 0, 'net_votes': 0, 'root_author': 'adsactly', 'root_permlink': 'adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers', 'max_accepted_payout': '1000000.000 SBD', 'percent_steem_dollars': 10000, 'allow_replies': True, 'allow_votes': True, 'allow_curation_rewards': True, 'beneficiaries': [], 'url': '/poetry/@adsactly/adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers#@josemalavem/pwe1h4', 'root_title': 'ADSactly Poetry: Poetry: A Place of Many Answers', 'pending_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'total_pending_payout_value': '0.000 STEEM', 'active_votes': [], 'replies': [], 'author_reputation': '18347752858813', 'promoted': '0.000 STEEM', 'body_length': 0, 'reblogged_by': []}

{'id': 79394594, 'author': 'owasco', 'permlink': 're-adsactly-pwpfqa', 'category': 'poetry', 'parent_author': 'adsactly', 'parent_permlink': 'adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers', 'title': '', 'body': "Very very beautifully written. You speak of your passion as a reader, but clearly you have passion for writing as well. I love, for instance, one of your first statements:

*With the rain it is as if the world stops and hearts open*

I do feel that, but have never heard it said quite so well. The very air can become still and the only sound the roar of the rain. I remember spending long days reading in the rain! I have not done this for a very long time, possibly since I no longer have a porch for cover during a good rain, but I'm going to take a book of poetry out to the tiny porch I do have and read the next time it rains. 

Maybe it will be a book by Antonia Palacios, because her writing is very beautiful. The first line of hers that you provided *I am here in the dark with my back to the light* is exceptional. 

", 'json_metadata': '{"tags":["poetry"],"app":"steempeak/1.14.19"}', 'last_update': '2019-08-23T19:34:57', 'created': '2019-08-23T19:34:57', 'active': '2019-08-23T19:34:57', 'last_payout': '2019-08-30T19:34:57', 'depth': 1, 'children': 0, 'net_rshares': 0, 'abs_rshares': 0, 'vote_rshares': 0, 'children_abs_rshares': 0, 'cashout_time': '1969-12-31T23:59:59', 'max_cashout_time': '1969-12-31T23:59:59', 'total_vote_weight': 0, 'reward_weight': 10000, 'total_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'curator_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'author_rewards': 0, 'net_votes': 0, 'root_author': 'adsactly', 'root_permlink': 'adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers', 'max_accepted_payout': '1000000.000 SBD', 'percent_steem_dollars': 10000, 'allow_replies': True, 'allow_votes': True, 'allow_curation_rewards': True, 'beneficiaries': [], 'url': '/poetry/@adsactly/adsactly-poetry-poetry-a-place-of-many-answers#@owasco/re-adsactly-pwpfqa', 'root_title': 'ADSactly Poetry: Poetry: A Place of Many Answers', 'pending_payout_value': '0.000 SBD', 'total_pending_payout_value': '0.000 STEEM', 'active_votes': [], 'replies': [], 'author_reputation': '49245444840965', 'promoted': '0.000 STEEM', 'body_length': 0, 'reblogged_by': []}

We have just given you a free upvote!

You have accordingly been rewarded 43.4675 AFIT tokens for your effort in reaching 10267 activity, as well as your user rank and report quality!
You also received an 0.36% upvote via @actifit account. 
Actifit rewards and upvotes are based on your:
- User rank: which depends on your delegated SP, accumulated AFIT tokens, rewarded post count and recent rewarded activity.
- Post score: which depends on your activity count, post content, post upvotes, quality comments, moderator review and user rank.

To improve your user rank, delegate more, pile up more AFIT tokens, and post more.
To improve your post score, get to the max activity count, work on improving your post content, improve your user rank, engage with the community to get more upvotes and quality comments.

Actifit rewards and upvotes are based on your:

- Post score: which depends on your activity count, post content, post upvotes, quality comments, moderator review and user rank.
